DURBAN - A seven-year-old school boy was killed when a minibus taxi collided with the car in which he was travelling in Durban on Tuesday.Rescue Care Paramedics spokesman Garrith Jamieson said the crash at the intersection of Blamey Road and South Coast Road also left a four-year-old boy in a critical condition.Jamieson said that the seven-year-old went into cardiac arrest shortly after paramedics arrived on the scene. They tried desperately to resuscitate him, but to no avail. He was declared dead at the scene.A pedestrian and a passenger were also injured in the collision.All the injured were taken to nearby hospitals. Police are investigating the accident.Africa News Agency